## T-021@20260416T043834Z — Complete

### What was built

**New module: `my-claw/tools/senseweave/self_critique.py`** — pre-performance self-critique with bounded revision passes.

### Architecture

Three functions forming a pipeline:

1. **`preview_score(score)`** — converts a `Score` to frequency events offline (no audio playback) and runs them through the ear engine to produce the full metrics dict (interval variety, hook clarity, development score, feedback scores, etc.)

2. **`critique_score(score, thresholds)`** — wraps `preview_score()` and gates against configurable thresholds. Default thresholds: `underdeveloped_score > 0.7`, `static_score > 0.7`, `development_score < 0.25`, `hook_clarity < 0.2`. Returns a `CritiqueReport` with pass/fail and which metrics failed.

3. **`revise_score(mood, **kwargs)`** — generates an initial score via `score_from_mood()`, critiques it. If it passes, returns immediately. If it fails, generates ONE rewrite with an incremented variation seed. Accepts the revision only if: (a) identity is preserved (same key, mood, tempo), and (b) at least one failed metric improved. Returns a `RevisionResult` with `.final_score` accessor.

